div.div: Civilization is dead, but Chito and Yuuri are still alive. So they hop aboard their beloved Kettenkrad motorbike and aimlessly wander the ruins of the world they once knew. Day after hopeless day, they look for their next meal and fuel for their ride. But as long as the two are together, even an existence as bleak as theirs has a ray or two of sunshine in it, whether they're sucking down their fill of soup or hunting for machine parts to tinker with. For two girls in a world full of nothing, the experiences and feelings the two share give them something to live forâ€¦ (Source: Yen Press) Note: Winner of the Best Comic Award at the Seiun Awards in 2019.
Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu: Dai-4 Shou - Seiiki to Gouyoku no Majo
Action, Adventure, Comedy, Drama, Fantasy, Romance

The 4th arc of the Re:Zero kara Hajimeru Isekai Seikatsu manga.
Subaru and Emilia go to the Sanctuary, a village within Roswaal's territory. There, they must pass trials made by Echidna, the Witch of Greed, to free Irlam's villagers.

In an age when the corners of the world have been scoured for their secrets, only one place remains unexploredâ€“a massive cave system known as the Abyss. Those who traverse its endless pits and labyrinth-like tunnels are known as Cave Raiders. A young orphan named Riko dreams of following in her motherâ€™s footsteps as a Cave Raider, and when she meets a strange robot when exploring the Abyss, sheâ€™s one step closer to achieving her goal! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment) Notes: - Includes the 4-chapter "How Are You? Somewhere" side story. - Nominated for the 11th Manga Taishou Awards (2018).

Naofumi Iwatani, an uncharismatic Otaku who spends his days on games and manga, suddenly finds himself summoned to a parallel universe! He discovers he is one of four heroes equipped with legendary weapons and tasked with saving the world from its prophesied destruction. As the Shield Hero, the weakest of the heroes, all is not as it seems. Naofumi is soon alone, penniless, and betrayed. With no one to turn to, and nowhere to run, he is left with only his shield. Now, Naofumi must rise to become the legendary Shield Hero and save the world!
(Source: One Peace Books)

In this new action-comedy, everything about a young man named Saitama screams "AVERAGE,” from his lifeless expression, to his bald head, to his unimpressive physique. However, this average-looking fellow doesn't have your average problem... He's actually a superhero that's looking for tough opponents! The problem is, every time he finds a promising candidate he beats the snot out of them in one punch. Can Saitama finally find an evil villain strong enough to challenge him? Follow Saitama through his hilarious romps as he searches for new bad guys to challenge!
(Source: Viz Media)
Action, Comedy, Drama, Romance, Sci-Fi, Supernatural

Ghosts, monsters, aliens, teen romance, battles...and the kitchen sink! This series has it all! Takakura, an occult maniac who doesn't believe in ghosts, and Ayase, a girl who doesn't believe in aliens, try to overcome their differences when they encounter the paranormal! This manga is out of this world! (Source: MANGA Plus) Notes: - Includes 1 extra chapter. - Nominated for the 15thÂ Manga Taisho Award in 2022.

Action, Comedy, Drama, Mecha, Romance, Sci-Fi

Sato Takahiro was an ordinary office worker and hobbyist gamer until the day he woke up on a spaceshipâ€“one that strangely resembled a craft from a favorite space-shooter game. With a decked-out ship, a crew full of babes, and a fantastic universe to explore, heâ€™s going to make the most of his good luck and create the life heâ€™s always dreamed of!
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)

Rumors revolving around The Book of Vanitas, a clockwork grimoire of dubious reputation, draw NoÃ©, a young vampire in search of a friend's salvation, to Paris. What awaits him in the City of Flowers, however, is not long hours treading the pavement or rifling through dusty bookshops in search of the tome. Instead, his quarry comes to him...in the arms of a man claiming to be a vampire doctor! Thrust into a conflict that threatens the peace between humans and vampires, will NoÃ© cast in his lot with the curious and slightly unbalanced Vanitas and his quest to save vampirekind? (Source: Yen Press)

As players of Monster Hunter and Dungeons & Dragons know, the slime is not exactly the king of the fantasy monsters. So when a 37-year-old Tokyo salaryman dies and wakes up in a world of dragons and magic, he's a little disappointed to find he's become a blind, boneless slime monster. (Source: Kodansha USA) Note: Chapter count includes 2 bonus chapters.
